# Stock Analyzer — Agent Rules

## Stack
- Backend: FastAPI + Pydantic v2 + SQLAlchemy async + Alembic
- Cache: Redis with aioredis, TTL-based (60s quotes, 1h history, 24h fundamentals)
- Queue: Celery + Redis broker
- Data: yfinance for market data, pandas-ta for indicators
- Auth: JWT via python-jose + passlib bcrypt
- Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + TanStack Query + Zustand + Recharts + lightweight-charts

## Hard Rules
- Always use async/await — never block the event loop
- All endpoints must return typed Pydantic response models
- Never hardcode secrets — use Pydantic BaseSettings from .env
- Use structlog for all logging, never print()
- All external API calls must use tenacity retry (3 attempts, exponential backoff)
- WebSocket auth via JWT query param (browsers can't set WS headers)

## Structure
- /backend/app/api/v1/ — route handlers only, no business logic
- /backend/app/services/ — all business logic lives here
- /backend/app/models/ — SQLAlchemy ORM
- /backend/app/schemas/ — Pydantic request/response schemas
- /frontend/src/hooks/ — all data fetching via custom hooks
- /frontend/src/api/ — Axios client + typed API functions
- /frontend/src/store/ — Zustand global state only